This paper is about spatial modeling of wireless information networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and simulation tools, which could be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MA). The paper also proposes a new deployment algorithm, which could be relevant to spatial informatics (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
